-- HSBC suspends 2 FX traders, Citi puts 2 on leave
-- By Steve Slater and Clare Hutchison
-- Fri Jan 17, 2014 10:59AM EST
-- None



LONDON, Jan 17 (Reuters) - HSBC Holdings <HSBA.L> said it had suspended two foreign exchange traders in London on Friday and Citigroup <C.N> said it had put a pair of traders on leave as the global probe into possible manipulation in currency markets stepped up.

"HSBC can confirm the suspensions of two foreign exchange traders in London," a spokesman for the bank said. He declined to comment further. A Citigroup spokesman said two FX traders had been put "on leave". He declined further comment.